Univariate Analysis

What is the structure of your dataset?

Our data set red wine comnsists of 1599 obs. of 12 variables. Attribute information: Input variables (based on physicochemical tests): 1 - fixed acidity (tartaric acid - g / dm^3) 2 - volatile acidity (acetic acid - g / dm^3) 3 - citric acid (g / dm^3) 4 - residual sugar (g / dm^3) 5 - chlorides (sodium chloride - g / dm^3 6 - free sulfur dioxide (mg / dm^3) 7 - total sulfur dioxide (mg / dm^3) 8 - density (g / cm^3) 9 - pH 10 - sulphates (potassium sulphate - g / dm3) 11 - alcohol (% by volume) Output variable (based on sensory data): 12 - quality (score between 0 and 10)

The following observations are made from dataSet: - the quality is normal distribution range from 3 to 8. - alcohol seems to be right skewd over range from 8.40 to 14.90. - ph is normal distribuation with mean 3.31. - minimume rate of alcohol in red wine is 8.40. - 25% of red wine has quality grater than 6.

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?

The main features of interst in our data set are red wine quality and alcohol volume.

What other features in the dataset do you think will help support your into your feature(s) of interest?

May be these variables will help support our investigation : total sulfur dioxid, free sulfur dioxide and residual sugar.

Did you create any new variables from existing variables in the dataset?

No.

Of the features you investigated, were there any unusual distributions? you perform any operations on the data to tidy, adjust, or change the form the data? If so, why did you do this?

Depend on the above plots some are normal distribution like PH and density, some right skewed like residual sugar and total sulfur dioxide.

Reflection

Our study about the quality of red wine, our data set has 1599 of red wine samples and 12 Attribute informations. First i starting reading the test file attached which describes the variables and how the data was collected in order to understand the variables and the data. I wished if there was specific categorical for the alcohol volume (standard text levels) beside the numeric volume Instead of guessing it ourselves.

The red wine quality study is a complex study, what is surprising that some relationship between variables have high correlation coefficient and has no insights or special impact for the red wine quality.

Finally, There is no specific factor that determine the quality of the red wine, Actually the quality of red wine determined by several factors generally increase alcohol volume, reduce density, reduce volatile acidity and increase citric acid.
